The paper deals with the analysis of blind-spot probability in a localization network, which involves wireless communication and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves modeling and analysis of a network, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper discusses the impact of correlated blocking on the network, which is related to control and systems engineering, falling under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and analysis, which falls under cs.MA (Mathematical Software). Finally, the paper involves the development of a new framework, which can be considered as a machine learning or statistical learning problem, falling under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
